-- Xylem Chief Executive McClain’s Pay Dropped 29 Percent in 2012
-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   M a r t i n
-- 2013-03-06T15:44:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-06/xylem-chief-executive-mcclain-s-pay-dropped-29-percent-in-2012.html
Xylem Inc. (XYL) , a maker of water
treatment systems, reduced pay for Chief Executive Officer
Gretchen McClain by 29 percent last year absent one time stock
awards related to the company’s 2011 spin-off from ITT Corp.  McClain’s total compensation dropped to $6.2 million last
year from $8.78 million in 2011, the White Plains, New York-
based company said today in a regulatory filing. Her base salary
increased 48 percent to $935,000.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christopher Martin in  New York  at 
 cmartin11@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
